\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 118. C. subtilis} Bertol.,{\i  Fl. Ital.}{\b  9}: 451 (1853). Perennial. Stems 10-30 cm, sparingly branched. Leaves white-tomentose; lower 1-pinnatisect. Capitula solitary. Involucre 7-11 mm in diameter; appendages with an appressed apical spine 0·5-1 mm, the fimbriae 0·5 mm. Florets purple. Pappus 1-2 mm, 1/3-1/2 as long as achene.{\i  Calcareous rocks. • S.E. Italy }({\i Mte. Gargano}). It.
\par

