\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 119. C. exarata} Boiss. ex Cosson, {\i Not. Pl. Crit. }116 (1851). Perennial. Stems 30-40 cm, erect, simple or sparingly branched. Lower leaves undivided, oblong-lanceolate, arachnoid; upper linear-lanceolate. Capitula solitary. Involucre 14-18 × 8-13 mm, ovoid; bracts appressed; appendages narrowly triangular, reddish-brown, erect, long-fimbriate, the apex c. 2 mm, not spinose. Florets purple. Pappus 1·5-2 mm, c. ½ as long as achene. •{\i  Portugal, S.W. Spain.} Hs Lu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 120. C. maculosa} Lam.,{\i  Encycl. Méth. Bot.}{\b  1}: 669 (1785). Biennial. Stems 20-60 cm, erect, paniculately branched. Leaves greenish, with arachnoid indumentum or glabrous; lower 2-pinnatisect, with lanceolate segments. Capitula solitary. Involucre 9-15 × 8-15 mm; bracts with prominent veins on dorsal surface; appendages pale brown, sometimes with a black spot at the base; fimbriae 2-3 mm, 6-12 on each side. Florets pink. Pappus 0·5-2 mm, 1/5-1/2 as long as achene. 2n = 18. •{\i  From C. France eastwards to S. Germany and N. Italy.} Au Ga Ge He It.
\par

