\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 121. C. vallesiaca} (DC.) Jordan,{\i  Pug. Pl. Nov.} 111 (1852). Biennial. Stems 25-70 cm, much-branched from the middle. Leaves greyish-green; lower 2-pinnatisect, with oblong to linear segments. Involucre 8-10 mm in diameter; appendages not covering the bracts, pale brown, sometimes with a small black centre, with an apical mucro up to 0·5 mm, the fimbriae 1-2 mm, 3-5 on each side, the lower forming a large auricle. Florets pink. Pappus c. 1 mm, c. 1/3 as long as achene. •{\i  S.W. Alps.} Ga He It.
\par

